Because according to several people who work in palliative care, major events take place in the midst of these regressions.
The patients admitted to the Victor-Gadbois palliative care home all suffer from cancer.
You have a maximum life expectancy of three months.
At this stage, the doctors and nurses who take care of them no longer shower them with so-called "healing" care.
