The server www.bankovnipoplatky.com, which annually announces a survey about the most absurd bank fees, has this year decided to organize the competition "Absurdest regulation or idea from the EU workshop".
“This was the idea behind the EU’s recent plan to introduce a 40% female quota in the management of large European companies,” Patrik Nacher, who is responsible for organizing the survey, told Pr<0xC3><0xA1>vo newspaper.
Among the nominated absurdities is, for example, the judgment of the European Court of Justice on the standardisation of insurance rates for men and women.
Until then, women enjoyed an advantage in life insurance because they objectively represented a lower risk to the insurance companies.
"Further incredible ideas from the EU workshop can be nominated by the end of this year.
