Infectious diseases and HIV/AIDS expert Andrade Villanueva commented that since 2008, scientists have concluded that while AIDS is not a death sentence, years of survival and quality of life depended on the degree of impairment of the immune system of individuals at the start of treatment, and that those who are not drug-dependent have greater chances of counting: up to 30 years at a count of 200 CD4 and up to 30 years at a count of 200 CD4.
