Even if mortality has decreased significantly in recent years (in Mexico, the number of people dying from AIDS has decreased from 6,678 cases in 2007 to 4,862 in 2011 (ONUSIDA annual report), it is still true that 60 percent of the patients recorded in the national database have died since the appearance of AIDS.
